    {
        "type": "text",
        "text": "(a) The Tripos Encryption Standard (TES) is a block cipher optimized for use on UGPs (“undergraduate processors”). It operates on 4-bit blocks, written as hexadecimal digits (e.g., a ⊕ 9 = 3). For one particular key K, it implements the following permutation: ",
